@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

class Calculator {
  .. Basic Arithmetic (no type hints) ..
  + add(a, b): numeric
  + subtract(a, b): numeric
  + multiply(a, b): numeric
  + divide(a, b): numeric

  .. Power Operations ..
  + square(x: int|float): int|float
  + cube(x: int|float): int|float
  + power(base: int|float, exponent: int|float): int|float
  + factorial(n: int): int

  .. Root Operations ..
  + sqrt(x: int|float): float
  + cbrt(x: int|float): float

  .. Logarithmic Operations ..
  + log10(x: int|float): float
  + ln(x: int|float): float
}

note right of Calculator::divide
  Raises ZeroDivisionError when b == 0.
  Python's / operator raises natively —
  no explicit guard in implementation.
end note

note right of Calculator::factorial
  Strict validation: rejects bool, float,
  str, None, and negative int.
  Raises ValueError for all invalid inputs.
  Iterative computation for n >= 2.
end note

note right of Calculator::sqrt
  Raises ValueError if x < 0.
  Delegates to math.sqrt(x).
end note

note right of Calculator::cbrt
  Supports negative inputs via sign flip:
  -((-x)^(1/3)) when x < 0.
  Delegates to math.pow().
end note

note right of Calculator::log10
  Raises ValueError if x <= 0.
  Delegates to math.log10(x).
end note

note right of Calculator::ln
  Raises ValueError if x <= 0.
  Delegates to math.log(x).
end note

class "math\n(stdlib)" as math <<module>>

Calculator ..> math : <<use>>\nsqrt, cbrt, log10, ln

@enduml
